00:47:11.458 --> 00:47:14.318
from clusters express more TNF, more interferon gamma.

807
00:47:14.898 --> 00:47:18.578
But then the real killing assay on autologous tumor assays show that the

808
00:47:18.638 --> 00:47:21.918
singlets show very little activity, and the T cells from

809
00:47:22.178 --> 00:47:22.738
APC

810
00:47:24.158 --> 00:47:28.078
in green and tumor clusters in purple show much

811
00:47:28.218 --> 00:47:32.078
more killing activity. And we see this in all out of 11 patients that

812
00:47:32.118 --> 00:47:32.738
we've looked at,

813
00:47:33.798 --> 00:47:35.538
albeit to different degrees.

814
00:47:36.678 --> 00:47:40.578
On average, we see a ninefold increase in melanoma killing capacity

815
00:47:40.638 --> 00:47:43.278
by T cells from clusters in 11 patients.

816
00:47:44.258 --> 00:47:47.658
We also reproduce this in mice with PDXs in an autologous

817
00:47:48.438 --> 00:47:50.158
model with adoptive cell transfer.

818
00:47:51.098 --> 00:47:53.038
This is in collaboration with Jonas Nilsson,

819
00:47:54.198 --> 00:47:57.898
where we see that T cells from clusters infiltrate into the tumor much

820
00:47:58.018 --> 00:47:58.318
better

821
00:48:00.018 --> 00:48:03.558
than single T cells. They're more activated, and there's much more

822
00:48:03.578 --> 00:48:07.538
expression of PD-L1 in the tumor microenvironment, suggesting

823
00:48:07.598 --> 00:48:10.718
that there's a lot of interferon gamma being secreted by those T cells.

824
00:48:11.558 --> 00:48:15.518
And this correlates with better killing capacity if you do adoptive cell

825
00:48:15.538 --> 00:48:18.418
transfer with T cells from clusters where the tumor

826
00:48:20.678 --> 00:48:24.478
APC clusters relative to single T cells, which do not

827
00:48:24.538 --> 00:48:26.298
show a lot of killing activity here.

828
00:48:28.418 --> 00:48:31.918
So we can identify, isolate, and visually confirm these

829
00:48:31.998 --> 00:48:35.918
clusters. They're associated with T cells that have different types and

830
00:48:35.978 --> 00:48:38.938
different cell states. I didn't have time to show you the data,

831
00:48:38.978 --> 00:48:42.882
butWith the TCR sequencing data, we have T

832
00:48:42.982 --> 00:48:43.302
cells

833
00:48:44.442 --> 00:48:48.282
carrying identical TCRs, and they can bind either to an

834
00:48:48.342 --> 00:48:52.122
APC or to a tumor cell, and we can show

835
00:48:52.842 --> 00:48:53.852
that the TCRs,

836
00:48:54.902 --> 00:48:57.882
when the T cells are bound to APCs, are more exhausted.

837
00:48:58.442 --> 00:49:01.382
That those T cells are more exhausted than when they're bound to tumor cells.

838
00:49:03.002 --> 00:49:05.242
It also allows us to ask new questions, of course.

839
00:49:06.282 --> 00:49:09.142
So why are we the first to report this?

